1. ğŸ¯ Design Philosophy

Simple: clean syntax, easy to read.

Safe by default: immutability, strict typing.

Practical: arrays, loops, and conditionals out of the box.

Future-ready: extensible for structs, maps, classes later.

Version 1 stops at:
âœ… Variables & Arrays
âœ… Conditionals
âœ… Loops
âœ… Functions

2. ğŸ Program Structure

Every program must define a main function:

fn main() {
    print("Hello, Zinc!")
}


Execution always starts from main.

3. ğŸ”¢ Variables & Types
Declaration
let a: int = 10      // immutable, explicit type
let b = 20           // immutable, inferred type
var c = 30           // mutable variable


let â†’ immutable (default, safe).

var â†’ mutable.

Type annotation optional if inference works.

Supported Types

int (64-bit signed integer)

float (64-bit double precision)

bool (true / false)

string (UTF-8)

array<T> (dynamic arrays, homogenous elements)

Examples
let x: int = 42
var y = 3.14
let msg = "Hello"
let nums: array<int> = [1, 2, 3, 4]

4. ğŸ§® Expressions

Arithmetic: + - * / %

Comparison: == != < > <= >=

Boolean: && || !

String concatenation: "Hi" + " there"

5. ğŸ”€ Conditionals
If Statement
if x > 10 {
    print("big")
} else {
    print("small")
}

If Expression
let grade = if score > 90 { "A" } else { "B" }

6. ğŸ” Loops
While
var i = 0
while i < 5 {
    print(i)
    i = i + 1
}

For (array iteration)
for n in [1,2,3,4] {
    print(n)
}

Times (repeat N times)
times 5 {
    print("Hello")
}
times(5){
    print("Hello")
}

7. ğŸ§© Functions
Declaration
fn add(a: int, b: int): int {
    return a + b
}

Calling
let result = add(5, 7)
print(result)


8. ğŸ“¦ Arrays
Declaration
let nums = [1, 2, 3]
var names: array<string> = ["a", "b", "c"]

Access
print(nums[0])   // prints 1

Mutation
var nums = [1, 2, 3]
nums[1] = 42
print(nums[1])   // prints 42

9. ğŸ“ Scope

New block {} creates scope.

Variables shadow outer ones.

Example:

fn main() {
    let x = 10
    {
        let x = 20
        print(x)   // 20
    }
    print(x)       // 10
}